The paper discusses the complexity of constraint satisfaction problems and approximability of Max-CSPs, which are topics typically studied in computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of polymorphisms as a tool for characterizing tractability and approximability further suggests that the paper may fall under these categories.
